snippet.title: Formula for the Volume of a Cone: Video II (Tanton: Mathematics)
snippet.description: In this second video of "geometry formulas explained" we explain why the volume of a cone is 1/3 the volume of the cylinder that surrounds it. This is a bit of a meaty video and will take some work to follow properly - but the goods are all there.
